name: rdf_dart
desc: Support for working with RDF (Resource Description Framework) data in Dart.

name: BlankNode
desc: Represents a blank node in an RDF graph.

name: BlankNode.new
desc: Creates a new Blank Node.

name: hashCode
desc: The hash code for this object.

name: id
desc: The unique identifier for this blank node.

name: isBlankNode
desc: Returns true as this is a Blank Node.

name: isIRI
desc: Returns false as this is not an IRI.

name: isLiteral
desc: Returns true if this term is a literal, false otherwise.

name: isTripleTerm
desc: Returns true if this term is a triple term, false otherwise.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: termType
desc: Returns the TermType of this term.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: Dataset
desc: Represents an RDF Dataset, which is a collection of RDF graphs.

name: Dataset.new
desc: Creates a new empty Dataset.

name: addNamedGraph
desc: Adds a named graph to the dataset.

name: defaultGraph
desc: The default graph of the dataset.

name: namedGraphs
desc: The named graphs of the dataset.

name: removeNamedGraph
desc: Removes a named graph from the dataset.

name: DatatypeNotFoundException
desc:
Exception thrown when a required datatype IRI is not found in the registry
or is not supported by the library.

name: DatatypeNotFoundException.new
desc: Creates a new DatatypeNotFoundException for the specified datatypeIri.

name: datatypeIri
desc: The IRI of the datatype that was not found.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: Graph
desc: Represents an RDF graph, which is a collection of RDF triples.

name: add
desc: Adds a triple to this graph.

name: addAll
desc: Adds all the triples in the given iterable to this graph.

name: classicize
desc: Takes a RDF Full graph and converts it to an RDF Classic graph

name: contains
desc: Checks if this graph contains the given triple.

name: remove
desc: Removes a triple from this graph.

name: triples
desc: Returns the set of triples in this graph.

name: IRI
desc: Represents an Internationalized Resource Identifier (IRI) according to RFC 3987.

name: authority
desc: The authority component.

name: fragment
desc: The fragment identifier component.

name: hasAbsolutePath
desc: Whether the URI has an absolute path (starting with '/').

name: hasAuthority
desc: Whether the IRI has an authority component.

name: hasEmptyPath
desc: Whether the URI has an empty path.

name: hasFragment
desc: Whether the URI has a fragment part.

name: hasPort
desc: Whether the URI has an explicit port.

name: hasQuery
desc: Whether the URI has a query part.

name: hasScheme
desc: Whether the IRI has a scheme component.

name: hashCode
desc: The hash code for this object.

name: host
desc: The host part of the authority component.

name: isAbsolute
desc: Whether the IRI is absolute.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: path
desc: The path component.

name: pathSegments
desc: The ITI path split into its segments.

name: port
desc: The port part of the authority component.

name: query
desc: The query component.

name: queryParameters
desc:
The IRI query split into a map according to the rules
specified for FORM post in the HTML 4.01 specification section
17.13.4.

name: queryParametersAll
desc:
Returns the IRI query split into a map according to the rules
specified for FORM post in the HTML 4.01 specification section
17.13.4.

name: scheme
desc: The scheme component of the IRI.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: toUri
desc: Converts the IRI to it's canonical Uri encoding

name: userInfo
desc: The user info part of the authority component.

name: IRITerm
desc: Represents an Internationalized Resource Identifier (IRI).

name: IRITerm.new
desc: Creates a new IRI from the given value string.

name: hashCode
desc: The hash code for this object.

name: isBlankNode
desc: Returns true if this term is a blank node, false otherwise.

name: isIRI
desc: Returns true if this term is an IRI term, false otherwise.

name: isLiteral
desc: Returns true if this term is a literal, false otherwise.

name: isTripleTerm
desc: Returns true if this term is a triple term, false otherwise.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: termType
desc: Returns the TermType of this term.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: value
desc: The string value of this IRI.

name: InvalidLanguageTagException
desc:
Exception thrown when a language tag string is not well-formed according
to BCP 47 syntax.

name: InvalidLanguageTagException.new
desc: Creates a new InvalidLanguageTagException for the invalid languageTag.

name: languageTag
desc: The invalid language tag string.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: InvalidLexicalFormException
desc:
Exception thrown when a literal's lexical form is invalid according to the
rules of its specified datatype.

name: InvalidLexicalFormException.new
desc: Creates a new InvalidLexicalFormException.

name: cause
desc:
Optional underlying exception that caused this validation failure,
such as a FormatException during parsing.

name: datatypeIri
desc: The IRI of the datatype for which the lexicalForm is invalid.

name: lexicalForm
desc: The invalid lexical form encountered.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: InvalidTermException
desc: Base class for exceptions related to invalid RDF terms.

name: InvalidTermException.new
desc: Creates a new InvalidTermException with the given message.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: Literal
desc: Represents a literal value in an RDF graph.

name: Literal.new
desc: Creates a new Literal.

name: baseDirection
desc: The base text direction (optional, RDF 1.2).

name: datatype
desc: The datatype of the literal.

name: getCanonicalLexicalForm
desc: Returns the canonical lexical form according to the datatype's rules.

name: hashCode
desc:
Computes the hash code based on term equality rules.
Uses lexicalForm, datatype, language adn baseDirection.
Note: language?.hashCode handles null correctly. Locale hashCode
should be case-insensitive appropriate for language tags.

name: isBlankNode
desc: Returns true if this term is a blank node, false otherwise.

name: isIRI
desc: Returns true if this term is an IRI term, false otherwise.

name: isLiteral
desc: Returns true if this term is a literal, false otherwise.

name: isTripleTerm
desc: Returns true if this term is a triple term, false otherwise.

name: language
desc: The language tag of the literal (optional).

name: lexicalForm
desc: The original lexical form of the literal as provided during construction.

name: operator ==
desc: The equality operator.

name: termType
desc: Returns the TermType of this term.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: value
desc: The parsed value of the literal.

name: LiteralConstraintException
desc: Exception thrown for violations of RDF literal constraints.

name: LiteralConstraintException.new
desc:
Creates a new LiteralConstraintException with the given message
detailing the violated constraint.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: NQuadsCodec
desc:
A Codec for encoding and decoding RDF Dataset objects to and from
N-Quads formatted strings.

name: NQuadsCodec.new
desc: Creates an N-Quads codec.

name: decoder
desc: Returns the NQuadsDecoder for converting an N-Quads string to a Dataset.

name: encoder
desc: Returns the NQuadsEncoder for converting a Dataset to an N-Quads string.

name: NTriplesCodec
desc:
A Codec for encoding and decoding RDF triples according to the
N-Triples specification.

name: NTriplesCodec.new
desc: Creates an N-Triples codec.

name: decoder
desc: Returns the decoder of this, converting from T to S.

name: encoder
desc: Returns the encoder from S to T.

desc: Provides constants for the RDF vocabulary namespace (rdf:).

name: alt
desc: rdf:Alt - The class of alternatives (RDF containers).

name: bag
desc: rdf:Bag - The class of unordered bags (RDF containers).

name: compoundLiteral
desc:
rdf:CompoundLiteral - The class of Compound Literals (RDF 1.2).
Represents literals with both language and direction.

name: direction
desc: rdf:direction - The base direction component of an rdf:CompoundLiteral (RDF 1.2).

name: first
desc: rdf:first - The first item in an RDF list.

name: html
desc: rdf:HTML - The datatype for HTML content as a literal.

name: json

name: langString
desc: rdf:langString - The datatype of language-tagged string literals.

name: language

name: namespace
desc: The base namespace for the RDF vocabulary.

name: nil
desc: rdf:nil - The empty list.

name: object

name: predicate

name: property

name: reifies
desc:
rdf:reifies - Relates a triple term object to its reification subject (RDF 1.2).
See: https://www.w3.org/TR/rdf12-concepts/#section-triple-terms

name: rest
desc: rdf:rest - The rest of the RDF list (another list or rdf:nil).

name: seq
desc: rdf:Seq - The class of ordered sequences (RDF containers).

name: subject

name: tripleTerm

name: type
desc: rdf:type - The subject is an instance of a class.

name: value
desc: rdf:value - Idiomatic property used for structured values.

name: xmlLiteral
desc: rdf:XMLLiteral - The datatype for well-formed XML content as a literal.
